[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi! Is it possible to have this with typeclass inference? Is there a general method to look for that kind of thing?</p>",
        "id": 454338816,
        "sender_full_name": "Etienne Marion",
        "timestamp": 1722013408
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yup, exists.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">TopologicalSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">DiscreteTopology</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">synth</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WeaklyLocallyCompactSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- succeeds</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 454340238,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1722013807
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the general method is: start a new file with <code>import Mathlib</code>, then add a <code>variable</code> statement of the appropriate hypotheses you expect to need for the inferance, and finally add <code>#synth</code> followed by the instance you want.</p>",
        "id": 454340409,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1722013879
    },
